OVERVIEW: Add multiple files to specified groups and targets in batch

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli add-files [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <file-paths> ... [--group <group>] --targets <targets> ...

ARGUMENTS:
  <file-paths>            File paths to add (use file:group format for per-file
                          groups, or use --group for all files)

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  -g, --group <group>     Group to add all files to (not used with file:group
                          format)
  -t, --targets <targets> Target names to add files to
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

